HEADWORD: Cordyline
<hw>Cordyline</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of Asiatic and Pacific
trees or shrubs remarkable for the fact that fragments of the trunk will
regrow to form whole plants.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Cordyline</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
